3
00:02:42,519 --> 00:02:45,816
Well, here we are. I turn down here
at the next block.

4
00:02:45,865 --> 00:02:49,687
Thanks, mister. I'll get off there.

5
00:02:54,404 --> 00:02:57,136
- Want anything else?
- No.

6
00:02:57,185 --> 00:02:59,616
Hey, you!

7
00:03:01,279 --> 00:03:04,995
- Me?
- Yeah you. Where re you heading?

8
00:03:05,043 --> 00:03:06,239
East.

9
00:03:06,288 --> 00:03:09,404
Too bad. I thought if you was heading north
I might be able to help you out.

10
00:03:09,437 --> 00:03:13,604
I m pushing myself late tonight.
I don t like to ride alone at night.

11
00:03:13,679 --> 00:03:17,861
I am one of those guys who gotta talk
or I fall asleep.

12
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:20,322
My partner, he s got Lou to keep him company, but ...

13
00:03:20,371 --> 00:03:22,121
... I ain t got nobody at all.

14
00:03:22,170 --> 00:03:24,494
- Where re you coming from?
- West.

15
00:03:24,543 --> 00:03:25,866
Yeah sure, I know, but ...

16
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:27,256
... where? LA?

17
00:03:27,305 --> 00:03:29,649
- Maybe.
- I ve got a cousin out in LA ...

18
00:03:29,698 --> 00:03:32,810
- You don t say.
- Yeah. He s been out ...

19
00:03:32,859 --> 00:03:34,181
You're not much of a talker, are you?

20
00:03:34,230 --> 00:03:36,117
My mother taught me never to speak
to strangers.

21
00:03:36,165 --> 00:03:37,994
- Oh, wise guy is it.
- So what!?

22
00:03:38,042 --> 00:03:40,084
Okay, okay. Don t get sore.

23
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:43,323
Trying to be sociable. That s all.

24
00:03:43,372 --> 00:03:44,976
Hey, Grandma!

25
00:03:45,025 --> 00:03:49,066
Give me change for a dime, will you?.

26
00:03:56,238 --> 00:03:59,079
Let s have something quieter this time, Joe.
My head s splitting.

27
00:03:59,129 --> 00:04:02,730
It that what's wrong with it?

28
00:04:03,630 --> 00:04:05,191
Done with your coffee?

29
00:04:05,241 --> 00:04:08,952
No.
And don t rush me, will you?

30
00:04:14,684 --> 00:04:16,564
Hey, turn that off.
Will you turn that thing off?

31
00:04:16,614 --> 00:04:18,435
- What s eating you now?
- Yeah, what s eating you?

32
00:04:18,485 --> 00:04:20,515
- That music, it stinks.
- Oh, you don t like it, huh?

33
00:04:20,565 --> 00:04:22,836
- No. Turn it off!
- Now wait a minute, pal.

34
00:04:22,886 --> 00:04:24,336
That was mine, that penny.

35
00:04:24,387 --> 00:04:29,078
This is a free country,
and I play whatever I want to.

36
00:04:29,128 --> 00:04:30,288
OK.

37
00:04:30,338 --> 00:04:32,489
Sure, and if you don t like it,
you don t have to listen to it.

38
00:04:32,539 --> 00:04:34,389
And you can leave here any time, you want to.

39
00:04:34,439 --> 00:04:36,090
OK OK. I m sorry I am.

40
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:38,491
First good piece played tonight,
and you don t like it.

41
00:04:38,541 --> 00:04:42,852
Some people just ain t got any good taste.

42
00:04:52,015 --> 00:04:55,446
That tune...  That tune...

43
00:04:55,496 --> 00:04:57,896
Why was it always that rotten tune?

44
00:04:57,946 --> 00:05:03,088
Following me around, beating in my head,
never letting up.

45
00:05:04,888 --> 00:05:07,029
Did you ever want to forget anything?

46
00:05:07,079 --> 00:05:07,885
Did you ever want cut away a piece of your memory
or blot it out?

47
00:05:07,897 --> 00:05:08,248
You can t, you know.

48
00:05:08,260 --> 00:05:08,749
No matter how hard you try.

49
00:05:08,761 --> 00:05:09,191
You can change the scenery ...

50
00:05:09,203 --> 00:05:09,760
... but sooner or later,
you ll get a whiff of perfume or...

51
00:05:09,772 --> 00:05:10,482
... somebody will say a certain phrase,
or maybe hum something ...

52
00:05:10,494 --> 00:05:11,370
... and you re licked again.

53
00:05:11,401 --> 00:05:11,982
"I can t believe that you re in love with me

54
00:05:11,994 --> 00:05:12,479
I used to love that song, once.

55
00:05:12,491 --> 00:05:13,328
So did the customers back in the old
Break O  Dawn Club in New York.

56
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:14,295
I can t remember a night when I didn t get
at least 3 requests for it.

57
00:05:14,307 --> 00:05:14,619
Sue ...

58
00:05:14,631 --> 00:05:15,159
She was always was selling it too.

59
00:05:15,171 --> 00:05:15,930
Those were the days.

60
00:05:21,543 --> 00:05:22,388
Your eyes of blue, your kisses too

61
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,067
I never knew what they could do

62
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,079
I can't believe that you're in love with me

63
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,079
You're telling everyone I know

64
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,079
That I'm on your mind each place you go

65
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,079
They can't believe that you're in love with me.

66
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,079
I have always placed you far above me

67
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,079
I just can't imagine that you love me

68
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,079
And after all is said and done

69
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,079
To think that I'm the lucky one

70
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:39,551
I can't believe that you're in love with me.

71
00:05:53,914 --> 00:06:02,703
It wasn t much of a club, really.
You know the kind.

72
00:06:02,829 --> 00:06:08,227
A joint where you could have a sandwich
and a few drinks ...

73
00:06:08,353 --> 00:06:21,159
... and run interference for your girl
on the dance floor.

74
00:06:21,285 --> 00:06:30,676
I fronted the piano in there every night
from 8:00 until the place closed up ...

75
00:06:30,802 --> 00:06:36,225
... which usually meant 4:00 in the morning.

76
00:06:36,351 --> 00:06:46,772
A good job, as jobs went in those days.

77
00:06:50,865 --> 00:06:55,611
And then too ...

78
00:06:55,736 --> 00:06:59,452
... there was Sue.

79
00:06:59,578 --> 00:07:08,090
... who made working there a little like working in heaven.

80
00:07:08,216 --> 00:07:19,390
But how we felt about each other.
Well, there was nothing very unusual in that.

81
00:07:19,516 --> 00:07:26,998
I was an ordinary healthy guy,
and she was an ordinary healthy girl.

82
00:07:27,124 --> 00:07:35,687
And when you add those two together,
you get an ordinary healthy romance.

83
00:07:35,812 --> 00:07:40,458
Which is the old story ...

84
00:07:40,583 --> 00:07:46,333
... sure, but somehow ...

85
00:07:46,459 --> 00:07:51,032
... the most wonderful thing in the world.

86
00:07:56,794 --> 00:08:00,858
All in all, I was a pretty lucky guy.

87
00:08:11,899 --> 00:08:13,990
Mr Paderewsky, I presume ...

88
00:08:14,041 --> 00:08:15,030
It's beautiful.

89
00:08:15,081 --> 00:08:17,315
You re going to make Carnegie Hall your door.

90
00:08:17,366 --> 00:08:20,117
Yeah, as a janitor.

91
00:08:20,169 --> 00:08:22,049
I ll make my debut in the basement.

92
00:08:22,101 --> 00:08:24,317
I don t blame you for being bitter, darling but ...

93
00:08:24,369 --> 00:08:25,920
... you mustn t give up hope.

94
00:08:25,968 --> 00:08:27,722
- Why, some day ...
- Yeah, some day ...

95
00:08:27,770 --> 00:08:29,313
... if I don t get arthritis first.

96
00:08:29,363 --> 00:08:33,435
In the meantime, let s blow this trap.

97
00:08:51,028 --> 00:08:53,448
- Like to get something to eat, hon ?
- I don t think so, Al.

98
00:08:53,497 --> 00:08:56,614
I lose my appetite working in this fleabag.

99
00:08:56,664 --> 00:08:59,451
- Let's go home.
- OK.

100
00:08:59,501 --> 00:09:02,110
I can t stand much more of that dump.

101
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:04,778
Did you see that drunk tonight trying to paw me.

102
00:09:04,828 --> 00:09:05,973
No, what drunk?

103
00:09:06,023 --> 00:09:09,079
It doesn t matter what drunk!

104
00:09:09,129 --> 00:09:11,466
Say, what s the matter with you tonight, darling?

105
00:09:11,516 --> 00:09:14,935
That s the third time you started
to tell me something and then stopped.

106
00:09:14,986 --> 00:09:17,565
We shouldn t have any secrets from each other, Sue.

107
00:09:17,616 --> 00:09:20,094
Next week, we re going to make with the ring and
the license. You and me. We ll be a team.

108
00:09:20,145 --> 00:09:23,260
Yes, that's right. In the Bush League.

109
00:09:23,310 --> 00:09:27,366
- I don t get you.
- We ve been struck out.

110
00:09:27,417 --> 00:09:29,187
A funny way to talk, darling.

111
00:09:29,238 --> 00:09:32,404
- Don t you want to marry me?
- Al, look, I love you, you know I do.

112
00:09:32,454 --> 00:09:35,175
- And I want to marry you.
- But ...

113
00:09:35,226 --> 00:09:36,703
But not now.

114
00:09:36,753 --> 00:09:39,413
Only after we do good.

115
00:09:39,464 --> 00:09:41,608
Someday, I'm going away.

116
00:09:41,659 --> 00:09:43,579
Oh, I know you ll think it silly ...

117
00:09:43,629 --> 00:09:47,837
That s why I hesitated to tell you.
But I m going to California ...

118
00:09:47,887 --> 00:09:50,294
I want to try my luck in Hollywood.

119
00:09:50,344 --> 00:09:52,741
That s the most stupid thing, I ever heard of.

120
00:09:52,791 --> 00:09:56,343
Don t you know millions of people go out there
every year and wind up polishing cuspidors?

121
00:09:56,392 --> 00:09:57,556
I thought you had better sense.

122
00:09:57,606 --> 00:09:59,459
You sound as if you don t think I have any talent.

123
00:09:59,507 --> 00:10:00,716
That has nothing to do with it.

124
00:10:00,764 --> 00:10:03,634
- I'll make out alright.
- Maybe. But what about me?

125
00:10:03,682 --> 00:10:06,144
Doesn t it mean anything to you that
you re busting up all our plans.

126
00:10:06,192 --> 00:10:09,248
- We may not see each other for years.
- It won t be that long.

127
00:10:09,293 --> 00:10:13,205
- I thought you loved me.
- I do, you know I do.

128
00:10:14,159 --> 00:10:14,550
Well ... here we are.

129
00:10:14,701 --> 00:10:14,929
Al ...

130
00:10:14,935 --> 00:10:15,200
Al, why can t you see my side of it?

131
00:10:15,205 --> 00:10:15,506
I'm young. We both are.

132
00:10:15,512 --> 00:10:15,944
And we ve got all the time in the world to settle down.

133
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:16,106
Really, darling ...

134
00:10:16,111 --> 00:10:16,510
... what I m doing is the only sane thing to do.

135
00:10:16,515 --> 00:10:16,943
I ...
I hate the thought of being so far away from you, but ...

136
00:10:16,948 --> 00:10:17,273
But we'll be together again someday.

137
00:10:17,278 --> 00:10:17,605
Maybe you ll decide to come out too, later on.

138
00:10:17,610 --> 00:10:17,754
So long.

139
00:10:17,759 --> 00:10:19,738
Al ...

140
00:10:19,798 --> 00:10:23,153
Aren t you going to kiss me goodnight?

141
00:10:23,213 --> 00:10:26,555
Sure, why not?

142
00:10:28,076 --> 00:10:31,225
Good night.

143
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:38,707
Say Roberts, you hit the jackpot this time ...

144
00:12:38,767 --> 00:12:40,830
Ten bucks.

145
00:12:40,891 --> 00:12:43,774
Thanks.

146
00:12:49,699 --> 00:12:52,224
But when a drunk handed me a ten spot,
after a request ...

147
00:12:52,276 --> 00:12:53,928
... I couldn t get very excited.

148
00:12:53,980 --> 00:12:57,803
What was it? I asked myself.
A piece of paper crawling with germs.

149
00:12:57,855 --> 00:13:02,562
It couldn t buy anything I wanted.
It couldn t ...

150
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:08,640
Then I thought of something.

151
00:13:30,876 --> 00:13:34,637
Long distance.
I d like to put a call through to Los Angeles.

152
00:13:34,689 --> 00:13:38,887
Miss Harvey, Sue Harvey. H-A-R-V-E-Y.

153
00:13:39,188 --> 00:13:43,095
The number is: Crest View 65723.

154
00:14:04,821 --> 00:14:09,787
Fifty ... seventy five ... eighty five.

155
00:14:11,751 --> 00:14:14,484
Hello Sue? This is Al.

156
00:14:14,536 --> 00:14:16,801
Oh baby, it s great to hear from you too.

157
00:14:16,853 --> 00:14:18,411
What s that? You do?

158
00:14:18,463 --> 00:14:20,302
Oh, me too, darling.

159
00:14:20,354 --> 00:14:23,108
I thought I d go batty without you.
I just had to ...

160
00:14:23,159 --> 00:14:27,513
Huh? ... You re working as a hash slinger?

161
00:14:27,565 --> 00:14:28,739
Gee honey, that s tough.

162
00:14:28,791 --> 00:14:32,385
Those guys out in Hollywood don t know the real thing
when it s right in front of them.

163
00:14:32,435 --> 00:14:34,132
You just stick it out too, baby.

164
00:14:34,182 --> 00:14:37,836
Keep going around to those casting offices.
I m sure you ll click.

165
00:14:37,886 --> 00:14:40,878
Look, I ll tell you what. You stay put out there.
I'll come to you.

166
00:14:40,928 --> 00:14:43,629
No, do not try to stop me.
Just expect me.

167
00:14:43,679 --> 00:14:48,448
Train? Who knows. Train, plane, bus, magic carpet.
I'll be there if I have to crawl.

168
00:14:48,498 --> 00:14:51,931
If I have to travel by pogo stick.
And then ...

169
00:14:51,981 --> 00:14:56,087
... let s get married right away, huh?

170
00:14:56,238 --> 00:15:00,464
That s the stuff.
That's what I ve been wanting to hear you say.

171
00:15:00,515 --> 00:15:04,350
Well ... goodbye for now.

172
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:07,301
I ll be seeing you soon.

173
00:15:07,351 --> 00:15:09,379
Yeah.

174
00:15:09,429 --> 00:15:11,718
Bye.

175
00:15:15,352 --> 00:15:18,414
The only way I could cross country was to thumb rides.

176
00:15:18,464 --> 00:15:22,189
For even after hawking everything,
I only had enough money to eat.

177
00:15:22,239 --> 00:15:25,552
Money. You know what that is.

178
00:15:25,602 --> 00:15:28,696
The stuff you never have enough of.
Little green things with ...

179
00:15:28,746 --> 00:15:31,062
... George Washington s picture
that men slave for ...

180
00:15:31,111 --> 00:15:34,116
... commit crimes for, die for.

181
00:15:34,165 --> 00:15:36,181
It s the stuff that has caused more
trouble in the world ...

182
00:15:36,231 --> 00:15:38,327
... than anything else we ever invented.

183
00:15:38,377 --> 00:15:41,202
Simply because, there s too little of it.

184
00:15:41,251 --> 00:15:43,477
At least, I had too little of it.

185
00:15:43,527 --> 00:15:47,060
So it was me for the thumb.

186
00:16:01,581 --> 00:16:03,977
Ever done any hitchhiking?

187
00:16:04,027 --> 00:16:06,482
It's not much fun, believe me.

188
00:16:06,532 --> 00:16:08,847
Oh yeah, I know all about how it s an education ...

189
00:16:08,897 --> 00:16:12,839
... how to get to meet a lot of people
and all that. But me ...

190
00:16:12,889 --> 00:16:17,250
... from now on, I ll take my education
in college, or in PS-62, or I ll...

191
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:21,991
... send $ 1.98 in stamps for  Ten Easy Lessons .

192
00:16:29,347 --> 00:16:34,117
Thumbing rides may save your busfare,
but it s dangerous.

193
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:36,542
You never know what s in store for you,
when you hear the...

194
00:16:36,592 --> 00:16:38,778
... squeal of brakes.

195
00:16:38,828 --> 00:16:44,397
If only I had known what I was getting into,
that day in Arizona.

196
00:16:44,836 --> 00:16:48,698
Here, throw that in the back seat.

197
00:16:48,918 --> 00:16:53,389
Okay, let s go. Make sure that door s closed.

198
00:17:05,295 --> 00:17:06,872
You know, Emily Post ought to write a ...

199
00:17:06,922 --> 00:17:09,677
... book of rules for guys thumbing rides.

200
00:17:09,727 --> 00:17:13,459
Because, as it is now, you never know
what s right and what s wrong.

201
00:17:13,509 --> 00:17:17,401
We rode along for a little while, neither one
of us saying anything.

202
00:17:17,451 --> 00:17:19,377
I was glad of that.

203
00:17:19,427 --> 00:17:23,020
I never know what to say to strange people
driving cars.

204
00:17:23,070 --> 00:17:26,274
Then too, you can never tell if a guy wants to talk.

205
00:17:26,324 --> 00:17:30,515
A lot of rides have been cut short
because of a big mouth.

206
00:17:30,565 --> 00:17:35,276
So I kept my mouth shut until
he started opening up.

207
00:17:35,326 --> 00:17:40,346
Hand me that little box in the compartment,
will ya pal.

208
00:17:41,304 --> 00:17:44,677
Hold the wheel, will you.

209
00:17:53,919 --> 00:17:56,271
- How far are you going?
- L.A.

210
00:17:56,323 --> 00:17:58,480
Well, you re really travelling, aren t you?

211
00:17:58,531 --> 00:18:00,586
Yeah, but I don t expect to make it
for a couple of years ...

212
00:18:00,637 --> 00:18:02,087
... at the rate I ve been sporting rides.

213
00:18:02,129 --> 00:18:04,697
- Not much luck, huh?
- Sure, all bad.

214
00:18:04,739 --> 00:18:08,476
Not many people stop for a guy these days.
Afraid of a stick up, maybe.

215
00:18:08,526 --> 00:18:10,607
Well, you can t blame them.

216
00:18:10,657 --> 00:18:12,920
- Where are you coming from?
- New York.

217
00:18:12,970 --> 00:18:15,051
Well, New York!

218
00:18:15,101 --> 00:18:18,454
Well, you re in luck this time.
I m going all the way.

219
00:18:18,504 --> 00:18:21,292
Right through to Los Angeles.

220
00:18:21,342 --> 00:18:25,352
- You drive a car?
- Sure, if you re tired, let me know.

221
00:18:25,402 --> 00:18:28,008
I ll holla.

222
00:18:28,058 --> 00:18:30,179
I guess at least an hour passed before
I noticed ...

223
00:18:30,229 --> 00:18:32,623
... those deep scratches
in his right hand.

224
00:18:32,673 --> 00:18:34,148
They were wicked.

225
00:18:34,198 --> 00:18:37,955
Three puffy red lines, about a quarter
of an inch apart.

226
00:18:38,006 --> 00:18:41,419
He must have seen me looking at them,
because he said ...

227
00:18:41,470 --> 00:18:43,591
Beauties, aren t they?

228
00:18:43,641 --> 00:18:47,186
They re going to be scars some day.

229
00:18:47,236 --> 00:18:48,539
What an animal!

230
00:18:48,590 --> 00:18:51,882
Whatever it was, it must have been
pretty big and vicious to have done that.

231
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:54,053
Right on both counts, New York.

232
00:18:54,104 --> 00:18:57,184
I was tussling with the most dangerous animal
In the world...

233
00:18:57,235 --> 00:18:59,032
... a woman.

234
00:18:59,083 --> 00:19:00,679
Must have been Tarzan s mate.

235
00:19:00,729 --> 00:19:02,597
Looks like, you lost the bout.

236
00:19:02,648 --> 00:19:05,142
It certainly wasn t a draw.

237
00:19:05,193 --> 00:19:08,172
You know, there should be a law
against dangerous claws.

238
00:19:08,222 --> 00:19:09,081
Yeah.

239
00:19:09,131 --> 00:19:12,009
I tossed her out of the car on her ear.

240
00:19:12,060 --> 00:19:13,514
Was I wrong?

241
00:19:13,565 --> 00:19:16,423
Give a lift to a tomato, you expect her
to be nice, don t you?

242
00:19:16,473 --> 00:19:20,083
- Yeah.
- After all, what kind of a dame, thumbs rides?

243
00:19:20,133 --> 00:19:23,782
- Sunday school teacher?
- Yeah.

244
00:19:23,833 --> 00:19:25,637
A little witch.

245
00:19:25,687 --> 00:19:28,776
Must have thought, she was riding
with some fall guy.

246
00:19:28,826 --> 00:19:32,746
Not me who s been booking horses around race tracks,
since I was twenty.

247
00:19:32,796 --> 00:19:35,253
Ahh, I've known a million dames like her.

248
00:19:35,303 --> 00:19:38,471
- Two million.
- Yeah.

249
00:19:39,223 --> 00:19:42,181
Stopped the car, opened the door ...

250
00:19:42,231 --> 00:19:44,397
"Take another hour and stop here, sister", I told her.

251
00:19:44,447 --> 00:19:48,338
- That s the stuff
- As I was going on.

252
00:19:48,388 --> 00:19:53,531
If you want to see a real scar, brother,
get a load of this.

253
00:19:53,582 --> 00:19:54,985
Wow

254
00:19:55,035 --> 00:19:58,134
- I got that one duelling.
- Duelling?

255
00:19:58,184 --> 00:20:02,355
Yeah, just kidding of course.
My dad owned a couple of Franco-Prussian sabres.

256
00:20:02,405 --> 00:20:05,162
Kept them on the wall for decoration.

257
00:20:05,212 --> 00:20:11,309
Well one day, another kid and I took them down,
and the old man wasn t around... Had a duel.

258
00:20:11,359 --> 00:20:13,545
He hit me in the arm here.

259
00:20:13,595 --> 00:20:16,894
Pretty mean cut. Infection set in later.

260
00:20:16,944 --> 00:20:18,889
Yeah, I can see that.

261
00:20:18,939 --> 00:20:23,431
- Oh, give me that box again, will ya.
- Yeah.

262
00:20:33,237 --> 00:20:37,669
Pain made me lose my head, I guess...
Began slashing ...

263
00:20:37,719 --> 00:20:40,477
Before I knew it, I d put the other kid s eye out.

264
00:20:40,527 --> 00:20:41,991
That was tough.

265
00:20:42,041 --> 00:20:45,540
Oh, it was just an accident, of course.
You know how kids are.

266
00:20:45,590 --> 00:20:48,819
I got scared and decided I was going to
run away from home.

267
00:20:48,869 --> 00:20:52,830
Old man almost caught me, when I was
packing my duds.

268
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:56,269
The bloody rag I had wrapped around my wrist
hadn't caught his attention ...

269
00:20:56,319 --> 00:20:59,180
... he'd have seen the bundle for sure.

270
00:20:59,230 --> 00:21:02,263
So I beat it, when he was phoning for a doctor.

271
00:21:02,313 --> 00:21:04,739
That was fifteen   sixteen years ago.

272
00:21:04,790 --> 00:21:08,257
I haven t been home since.

273
00:21:10,723 --> 00:21:14,615
Pull in there for a bite of something, huh?
I ll buy you ...

274
00:21:14,665 --> 00:21:19,658
Brother, was I hungry.
I hadn t had anything in my stomach for hours.

275
00:21:19,709 --> 00:21:21,670
But even with that gnawing in the pit of my belly.

276
00:21:21,721 --> 00:21:25,248
I didn t want to be in too big a rush
to put on the feed bag.

277
00:21:25,299 --> 00:21:28,139
First, I had to make sure this guy knew the score.

278
00:21:28,190 --> 00:21:31,970
If I got him down on me, goodbye ticket to Hollywood.

279
00:21:32,021 --> 00:21:35,387
- I ll wait out here for you, mister.
- If it s the money, don t worry about paying for it.

280
00:21:35,437 --> 00:21:36,569
This time it s on me.

281
00:21:36,620 --> 00:21:38,874
- Well, that s quite ...
- Haskell. Think nothing of it.

282
00:21:38,925 --> 00:21:42,382
You make your first million, maybe you can
do the same for me. Come on, New York.

283
00:21:42,432 --> 00:21:44,151
I gotta make the West Coast by Wednesday.

284
00:21:44,201 --> 00:21:47,011
There s a horse running at Santa Anita,
named "Paradisical" ...

285
00:21:47,062 --> 00:21:50,863
- Means dough to for me, if I m on it.
- You ll make it, alright

286
00:21:50,913 --> 00:21:54,562
He did most of the talking, during the half hour
we were in the place.

287
00:21:54,613 --> 00:21:56,635
I ate.

288
00:21:56,685 --> 00:22:00,779
He rambled on about his old man, whom he hadn t
heard from since he ran away as a kid,...

289
00:22:00,830 --> 00:22:02,811
... and how he happened to become a bookie.

290
00:22:02,861 --> 00:22:05,540
And then all about how he got rooked in Miami.

291
00:22:05,590 --> 00:22:08,522
One race, 38 grand. They cleaned out my book.

292
00:22:08,572 --> 00:22:11,008
- How do you like that?
- It was tough luck.

293
00:22:11,059 --> 00:22:13,799
Yeah, and I'm supposed to be the smart guy.
You just wait ...

294
00:22:13,849 --> 00:22:16,369
I m going back to Florida, next season,
with all kinds of jack.

295
00:22:16,419 --> 00:22:19,399
And you watch those stinkers run for cover.

296
00:22:19,449 --> 00:22:23,199
- Want anything else?
- No thanks, I've had plenty.

297
00:22:27,499 --> 00:22:31,099
Got the cheque there, sister?

298
00:22:32,499 --> 00:22:34,449
Oh, just a minute! Your change, sir.

299
00:22:34,499 --> 00:22:37,239
- Keep it, sister.
- Oh, thank you, sir. Call again.

300
00:22:37,289 --> 00:22:40,469
I ll be waiting outside for you,
when you ve finished work.

301
00:22:40,519 --> 00:22:43,459
Sharp chick, huh?

302
00:22:49,769 --> 00:22:53,379
I drove all that night, while Haskell
slept like a log.

303
00:22:53,429 --> 00:22:57,669
After a while, I began to get sleepy myself.

304
00:22:57,719 --> 00:22:59,589
I was happy though.

305
00:22:59,639 --> 00:23:01,719
Soon I d be with Sue again.

306
00:23:01,769 --> 00:23:06,539
The long trip was practically over, and there d be
no more hoofing it down the concrete.

307
00:23:06,589 --> 00:23:08,919
I began to think of the future ...

308
00:23:08,969 --> 00:23:12,789
... which couldn t have been brighter
if I d embroidered it with neon lights.

309
00:23:12,839 --> 00:23:16,519
It was nice to think of Sue, shooting to the top.

310
00:23:16,569 --> 00:23:20,639
Hmpf ... It s amazing what a full belly can do
to your imagination.

311
00:23:23,339 --> 00:23:28,009
Your eyes of blue, your kisses too

312
00:23:28,059 --> 00:23:32,429
I never knew what they could do

313
00:23:32,479 --> 00:23:40,879
I can't believe that you're in love with me

314
00:23:40,929 --> 00:23:45,489
You're telling everyone I know

315
00:23:45,539 --> 00:23:49,949
I'm on your mind each place you go

316
00:23:49,999 --> 00:24:02,069
I can't believe that you're in love with me
